libfacerec
------------------------------------------
libfacerec is a library for face recognition in OpenCV. It has been merged
into OpenCV 2.4 (contrib module) and both implementations are synchronized. So
if you are in (a recent) OpenCV 2.4: There is no need to compile libfacerec
yourself, you have everything to get started. Note: Make sure to work on a
recent OpenCV revision, if you want to be compatible with the very latest
libfacerec version.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-1.7.33-1
  libgcc1-4.9.2-1
  libopencv2.4-2.4.9-1
  libopencv_facerec0-0.05-1bl1
  libstdc++6-4.9.2-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.24.51-6
  cmake-2.8.12.2-3
  cygport-0.17.1-1
  gcc-core-4.9.2-1
  gcc-g++-4.9.2-1
  make-4.0-2

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/bytefish/libfacerec

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/bytefish/libfacerec/archive/v0.05.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  unpack libfacerec-0.05-X-src.tar.xz
    if you use setup to install this src package, it will be
        unpacked under /usr/src automatically
  cd /usr/src
  cygport ./libfacerec-0.05-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/libfacerec-0.05-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libfacerec-0.05-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libopencv_facerec0-0.05-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libopencv_facerec-devel-0.05-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(libfacerec)
  /usr/bin/facerec_demo.exe
  /usr/bin/facerec_eigenfaces.exe
  /usr/bin/facerec_fisherfaces.exe
  /usr/bin/facerec_lbph.exe
  /usr/bin/facerec_video.exe
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/libfacerec.README
  /usr/share/doc/libfacerec/README.md

(libopencv_facerec0)
  /usr/bin/cygopencv_facerec-0.dll

(libopencv_facerec-devel)
  /usr/include/libfacerec/decomposition.hpp
  /usr/include/libfacerec/facerec.hpp
  /usr/include/libfacerec/helper.hpp
  /usr/include/libfacerec/lbp.hpp
  /usr/include/libfacerec/subspace.hpp
  /usr/lib/libopencv_facerec.dll.a

